<ns6113:section xmlns:ns6113="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.shell.shells">

	<ns6114:title xmlns:ns6114="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Shells</ns6114:title>
	<ns6115:para xmlns:ns6115="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	     A shell is a command interface to the operating system kernel. Commands entered 
          by the user are interpreted by the shell. Generally shells provide the the following features 
	</ns6115:para>
	<ns6116:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6116="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	<ns6117:listitem xmlns:ns6117="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	<ns6118:formalpara xmlns:ns6118="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns6119:title xmlns:ns6119="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Command line user interface</ns6119:title>
		<ns6120:para xmlns:ns6120="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		A shell provides channels for a user to interact with the application running within the shell.   
		</ns6120:para>
	</ns6118:formalpara>
	</ns6117:listitem>
	
	<ns6121:listitem xmlns:ns6121="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	<ns6122:formalpara xmlns:ns6122="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns6123:title xmlns:ns6123="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Environment configuration</ns6123:title>
		<ns6124:para xmlns:ns6124="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		  Many applications rely on environment variables which allow for the system wide or user 
		  specific configuration of parameters. Your <ns6125:quote xmlns:ns6125="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">favourite</ns6125:quote> editor is set in 
		  the <ns6126:quote xmlns:ns6126="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">EDITOR</ns6126:quote> environment variable. These environment settings can be 
		  configured system wide in the configuration directory (/etc/) or user specific in the users 
		  home directory. Various shells use different files to set the default environment variables. 
		  The commands used to access the environment configuration also vary between the 
		  different shells, although the concepts as well as the variables are often the same.
		</ns6124:para>
	</ns6122:formalpara>
	</ns6121:listitem>
	
	<ns6127:listitem xmlns:ns6127="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	<ns6128:formalpara xmlns:ns6128="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns6129:title xmlns:ns6129="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Programming</ns6129:title>
		<ns6130:para xmlns:ns6130="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     		Most shells provide the functionality to group a sequence of commands together 
    		into a script. These scripts can be used to perform all sorts of tasks and can make 
    		life so much easier for ourselves. Together with a rich set of utilities, scripts are 
    		capable of performing complex tasks. Scripts can also be nested, which means 
    		that scripts can make use of other scripts. Again the basic principle of providing 
    		tools focusing on a single purpose applies. 
		</ns6130:para>
	</ns6128:formalpara>
	</ns6127:listitem>
	
	<ns6131:listitem xmlns:ns6131="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	<ns6132:formalpara xmlns:ns6132="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns6133:title xmlns:ns6133="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">I / O redirection</ns6133:title>
		<ns6134:para xmlns:ns6134="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		The channeling of input and output is also controlled by the shell. Input to a program can 
		be obtained from a number of sources such as the keyboard, a file or the output of another 
		application. Similarly	output may be redirected to standard out (user), a file or another 
		program. This is achieved by using standard in (stdin), standard out (stdout), redirection 
		and pipes.
		</ns6134:para>	
	</ns6132:formalpara>
	</ns6131:listitem>
	
	</ns6116:itemizedlist>

	<ns6135:para xmlns:ns6135="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		The implementation of these features might differ slightly between 
		the various shells but the concepts are the same. 
	</ns6135:para>
	
	<ns6136:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6136="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		<ns6137:listitem xmlns:ns6137="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6138:formalpara xmlns:ns6138="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6139:title xmlns:ns6139="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Bourne shell</ns6139:title>
				<ns6140:para xmlns:ns6140="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				The simplest, most basic shell. Most modern shells have built on and extended 
				this shell.	It was developed by Steven Bourne at AT&amp;T Bell Laboratories.
				</ns6140:para>
			</ns6138:formalpara>
		</ns6137:listitem>
		<ns6141:listitem xmlns:ns6141="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6142:formalpara xmlns:ns6142="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6143:title xmlns:ns6143="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Korn shell</ns6143:title>
				<ns6144:para xmlns:ns6144="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				  As the korn shell is available commercially the open source community developed
				  the public domain korn shell (pdksh). 	
				  It was designed and developed by David G. Korn at AT&amp;T Bell Laboratories. 
				</ns6144:para>
			</ns6142:formalpara>
		</ns6141:listitem>
		<ns6145:listitem xmlns:ns6145="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6146:formalpara xmlns:ns6146="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6147:title xmlns:ns6147="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">C shell</ns6147:title>
				<ns6148:para xmlns:ns6148="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				  The C shell privides a C-like syntax and has added convenience over the bourne shell. 
				  Amongst the additions over to bourne shell was a history mechanism allowing access  
				  to previously used commands, job control to manage programs running in the 
				  background and interactive file name completion. It was developed at the 
				  University of Berkeley.
				</ns6148:para>
			</ns6146:formalpara>
		</ns6145:listitem>
		<ns6149:listitem xmlns:ns6149="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6150:formalpara xmlns:ns6150="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6151:title xmlns:ns6151="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">tcshell</ns6151:title>
				<ns6152:para xmlns:ns6152="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				  tcsh is an enhanced but completely compatible version of the Berkeley UNIX C shell. 
			  	 Amongst the enhancements is a command line editing and spelling correction.
				</ns6152:para>
			</ns6150:formalpara>
		</ns6149:listitem>
		<ns6153:listitem xmlns:ns6153="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6154:formalpara xmlns:ns6154="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6155:title xmlns:ns6155="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Bourne Again shell</ns6155:title>
				<ns6156:para xmlns:ns6156="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				  The bourne again shell (bash) is the default shell on most linux distributes. 
				  It is fully compatible with the bourne shell but also includes many additional 
				  features. Bash included many features from the korn shell as well as the c shell.
				</ns6156:para>
			</ns6154:formalpara>
		</ns6153:listitem>
	
		</ns6136:itemizedlist>
		
		
		<ns6157:section xmlns:ns6157="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6158:title xmlns:ns6158="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Common features</ns6158:title>
			<ns6159:para xmlns:ns6159="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			Although each shell has unique features, several commonalities can be found. 
			</ns6159:para>
			<ns6160:section xmlns:ns6160="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6161:title xmlns:ns6161="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Environment Variables</ns6161:title>
				<ns6162:para xmlns:ns6162="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				A set of environment variables are shared between the more popular shells.
				</ns6162:para>
				<ns6163:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6163="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6164:listitem xmlns:ns6164="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6165:formalpara xmlns:ns6165="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6166:title xmlns:ns6166="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">PATH : </ns6166:title>
					<ns6167:para xmlns:ns6167="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					A colon (:) separated list of directions which are searched for executables
					</ns6167:para>
				</ns6165:formalpara>	
				</ns6164:listitem>
				<ns6168:listitem xmlns:ns6168="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6169:formalpara xmlns:ns6169="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6170:title xmlns:ns6170="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">PWD : </ns6170:title>
						<ns6171:para xmlns:ns6171="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						Current working directory
						</ns6171:para>
					</ns6169:formalpara>
				</ns6168:listitem>	
				<ns6172:listitem xmlns:ns6172="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6173:formalpara xmlns:ns6173="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6174:title xmlns:ns6174="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">TERM : </ns6174:title>
						<ns6175:para xmlns:ns6175="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						Terminal type currently used
						</ns6175:para>
					</ns6173:formalpara>
				</ns6172:listitem>	
				<ns6176:listitem xmlns:ns6176="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6177:formalpara xmlns:ns6177="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6178:title xmlns:ns6178="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">USER : </ns6178:title>
						<ns6179:para xmlns:ns6179="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						User id of the currently logged on user
						</ns6179:para>
					</ns6177:formalpara>
				</ns6176:listitem>	
				<ns6180:listitem xmlns:ns6180="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6181:formalpara xmlns:ns6181="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6182:title xmlns:ns6182="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">EDITOR : </ns6182:title>
						<ns6183:para xmlns:ns6183="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						Preferred terminal editor
						</ns6183:para>
					</ns6181:formalpara>
				</ns6180:listitem>	
				<ns6184:listitem xmlns:ns6184="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6185:formalpara xmlns:ns6185="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6186:title xmlns:ns6186="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">HOSTNAME : </ns6186:title>
						<ns6187:para xmlns:ns6187="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						The hostname of the workstation
						</ns6187:para>
					</ns6185:formalpara>
				</ns6184:listitem>	
				<ns6188:listitem xmlns:ns6188="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6189:formalpara xmlns:ns6189="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6190:title xmlns:ns6190="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">SHELL : </ns6190:title>
						<ns6191:para xmlns:ns6191="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						The path to the shell executable currently in use
						</ns6191:para>
					</ns6189:formalpara>
				</ns6188:listitem>	
				</ns6163:itemizedlist>
			</ns6160:section>	
		</ns6157:section>	
		
		<ns6192:section xmlns:ns6192="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6193:title xmlns:ns6193="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Selecting a shell</ns6193:title>
			<ns6194:para xmlns:ns6194="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			  The users default shell is typically stored in the <ns6195:quote xmlns:ns6195="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">/etc/passwd</ns6195:quote> 
			  file, which is only accessible by the root user. This file is covered in more detail 
			  later on in the security section. 
			</ns6194:para>
			<ns6196:programlisting xmlns:ns6196="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
...
alex:x:502:100:Alexander Hartner:/home/alex:/usr/bin/tcsh
solms:x:503:100:Solms Training &amp; Consulting:/home/solms:/bin/bash
ldap:x:76:70:User for OpenLDAP:/var/lib/ldap:/bin/bash
named:x:44:44:Name server daemon:/var/lib/named:/bin/false
squid:x:31:65534:WWW-proxy squid:/var/cache/squid:/bin/false
...
			</ns6196:programlisting>
		  <ns6197:para xmlns:ns6197="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">	
			To change your own shell, the <ns6198:emphasis xmlns:ns6198="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">chsh</ns6198:emphasis> 
			command can be used. The default shell for users on Linux is bash.
			</ns6197:para>
			<ns6199:programlisting xmlns:ns6199="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
alex@chameleon:~&gt; chsh
Changing login shell for alex.
Password: 
Enter the new value, or press return for the default
        Login Shell [/bin/bash]: /usr/bin/tcsh
Shell changed.
alex@chameleon:~&gt; 
			</ns6199:programlisting>
		</ns6192:section>	

		<ns6200:section xmlns:ns6200="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6201:title xmlns:ns6201="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Which shell is right for me ?</ns6201:title>
			<ns6202:para xmlns:ns6202="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				The default shell allocated to newly created users is the bash, and provides a 
				user-friendly and intuitive interface to the user. Before trying out features offered 
				by other shells, novice users are suggested to first find their footing using bash. 
				Once the many commands available have been managed and a certain level of 
				confidence has been established, feel free to explore other shells. 
			</ns6202:para>
		</ns6200:section>	

		<ns6203:section xmlns:ns6203="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			<ns6204:title xmlns:ns6204="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Configuring your prompt</ns6204:title>
			<ns6205:para xmlns:ns6205="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
			The prompt is defined by three environment variables, <ns6206:emphasis xmlns:ns6206="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">PS1</ns6206:emphasis>, <ns6207:emphasis xmlns:ns6207="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">PS2</ns6207:emphasis>, <ns6208:emphasis xmlns:ns6208="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">PS3</ns6208:emphasis> and <ns6209:emphasis xmlns:ns6209="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">PS4</ns6209:emphasis>. PS1 represents the default prompt, PS2 is the secondary prompt, prompting for additional input. PS3 is used in a select loop. PS4 is shown on each line of a shell script executed with the -x option. To modify the prompt environment variable set the new value in your shells startup scripts. For bash, for example, a good place to set your prompt is ~/.bashrc. 
			</ns6205:para>
			<ns6210:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6210="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
				<ns6211:listitem xmlns:ns6211="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6212:formalpara xmlns:ns6212="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6213:title xmlns:ns6213="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\u</ns6213:title>
						<ns6214:para xmlns:ns6214="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The username</ns6214:para>
					</ns6212:formalpara>
				</ns6211:listitem>
				<ns6215:listitem xmlns:ns6215="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6216:formalpara xmlns:ns6216="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6217:title xmlns:ns6217="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\h</ns6217:title>
						<ns6218:para xmlns:ns6218="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The section of the hostname up to the first full stop</ns6218:para>
					</ns6216:formalpara>
				</ns6215:listitem>
				<ns6219:listitem xmlns:ns6219="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6220:formalpara xmlns:ns6220="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6221:title xmlns:ns6221="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\H</ns6221:title>
						<ns6222:para xmlns:ns6222="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The full hostname</ns6222:para>
					</ns6220:formalpara>
				</ns6219:listitem>
				<ns6223:listitem xmlns:ns6223="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6224:formalpara xmlns:ns6224="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6225:title xmlns:ns6225="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\w</ns6225:title>
						<ns6226:para xmlns:ns6226="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The username</ns6226:para>
					</ns6224:formalpara>
				</ns6223:listitem>
				<ns6227:listitem xmlns:ns6227="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6228:formalpara xmlns:ns6228="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6229:title xmlns:ns6229="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\d</ns6229:title>
						<ns6230:para xmlns:ns6230="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Current date in Weekday, Month Day format</ns6230:para>
					</ns6228:formalpara>
				</ns6227:listitem>
				<ns6231:listitem xmlns:ns6231="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6232:formalpara xmlns:ns6232="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6233:title xmlns:ns6233="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\D{FORMAT}</ns6233:title>
						<ns6234:para xmlns:ns6234="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						Current date formatted as specified. (see <ns6235:emphasis xmlns:ns6235="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">man strftime) for full information on format specification</ns6235:emphasis>
						</ns6234:para>
					</ns6232:formalpara>
				</ns6231:listitem>
				<ns6236:listitem xmlns:ns6236="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6237:formalpara xmlns:ns6237="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6238:title xmlns:ns6238="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\n</ns6238:title>
						<ns6239:para xmlns:ns6239="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">A newline character</ns6239:para>
					</ns6237:formalpara>
				</ns6236:listitem>
				<ns6240:listitem xmlns:ns6240="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6241:formalpara xmlns:ns6241="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6242:title xmlns:ns6242="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\j</ns6242:title>
						<ns6243:para xmlns:ns6243="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The number of jobs currently managed by the shell</ns6243:para>
					</ns6241:formalpara>
				</ns6240:listitem>
				<ns6244:listitem xmlns:ns6244="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6245:formalpara xmlns:ns6245="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6246:title xmlns:ns6246="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\e</ns6246:title>
						<ns6247:para xmlns:ns6247="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The escape character</ns6247:para>
					</ns6245:formalpara>
				</ns6244:listitem>
				<ns6248:listitem xmlns:ns6248="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6249:formalpara xmlns:ns6249="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6250:title xmlns:ns6250="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\r</ns6250:title>
						<ns6251:para xmlns:ns6251="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">carriage return</ns6251:para>
					</ns6249:formalpara>
				</ns6248:listitem>
				<ns6252:listitem xmlns:ns6252="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6253:formalpara xmlns:ns6253="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6254:title xmlns:ns6254="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\t</ns6254:title>
						<ns6255:para xmlns:ns6255="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Current time in 12 hour format (hh:mm:ss)</ns6255:para>
					</ns6253:formalpara>
				</ns6252:listitem>
				<ns6256:listitem xmlns:ns6256="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6257:formalpara xmlns:ns6257="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6258:title xmlns:ns6258="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\T</ns6258:title>
						<ns6259:para xmlns:ns6259="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Current time in 24 hour format (hh:mm:ss)</ns6259:para>
					</ns6257:formalpara>
				</ns6256:listitem>
				<ns6260:listitem xmlns:ns6260="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6261:formalpara xmlns:ns6261="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6262:title xmlns:ns6262="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\w</ns6262:title>
						<ns6263:para xmlns:ns6263="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">current working directory</ns6263:para>
					</ns6261:formalpara>
				</ns6260:listitem>
				<ns6264:listitem xmlns:ns6264="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6265:formalpara xmlns:ns6265="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6266:title xmlns:ns6266="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\!</ns6266:title>
						<ns6267:para xmlns:ns6267="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">history index key of current command</ns6267:para>
					</ns6265:formalpara>
				</ns6264:listitem>
				<ns6268:listitem xmlns:ns6268="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6269:formalpara xmlns:ns6269="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6270:title xmlns:ns6270="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\#</ns6270:title>
						<ns6271:para xmlns:ns6271="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">command number of command</ns6271:para>
					</ns6269:formalpara>
				</ns6268:listitem>
				<ns6272:listitem xmlns:ns6272="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
					<ns6273:formalpara xmlns:ns6273="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
						<ns6274:title xmlns:ns6274="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">\[ \]</ns6274:title>
						<ns6275:para xmlns:ns6275="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">begin and end of sequence of non-printable characters</ns6275:para>
					</ns6273:formalpara>
				</ns6272:listitem>
			</ns6210:itemizedlist>
		<ns6276:programlisting xmlns:ns6276="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
bumblebee root # export PS1="\u@\h \T &gt;"
root@bumblebee 08:45:34 &gt;
		</ns6276:programlisting>
	</ns6203:section>	
</ns6113:section>